Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Memory Safety Analysis Module

Provides static and dynamic analysis tools for memory safety, including leak, race, and overflow/underflow detection.

Features:
- Static and dynamic memory safety analysis
- Leak, race, overflow, and underflow detection
- Integration with custom allocators and GC
- Real-time safety monitoring
- AI/agent-friendly safety APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note

Note: Memory Safety Analysis Types and Interfaces
Type called "MemorySafetyAnalyzer":
    analyze_static as Function that takes code as String returns SafetyReport
    analyze_dynamic as Function that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns SafetyReport
    monitor_realtime as Function that takes profiler as MemoryProfiler returns SafetyReport
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SafetyReport":
    leaks as List[Pointer]
    races as List[String]
    overflows as List[String]
    underflows as List[String]
    summary as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Memory Safety Analysis Functions
Process called "analyze_static" that takes analyzer as MemorySafetyAnalyzer and code as String returns SafetyReport:
    Note: Performs static analysis for memory safety
    Return SafetyReport with:
        leaks as computed
        races as computed
        overflows as computed
        underflows as computed
        summary as computed
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "analyze_dynamic" that takes analyzer as MemorySafetyAnalyzer and profiler as MemoryProfiler returns SafetyReport:
    Note: Performs dynamic analysis for memory safety
    Return SafetyReport

Process called "monitor_realtime" that takes analyzer as MemorySafetyAnalyzer and profiler as MemoryProfiler returns SafetyReport:
    Note: Monitors memory safety in real time
    Return SafetyReport 